[1] India (Tamil Nadu): dog origin, human fatality
Date: Mon 23 Aug 2021
Source: The Hindu [edited]
https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/7-year-old-from-village-near-poonamallee-dies-of-rabies/article36051232.ece


A 7-year-old boy died of rabies on Saturday [21 Aug 2021] after he was bitten by a stray dog in Agaram Mel village, near Poonamallee, in Tiruvallur district [Tamil Nadu].

The victim was identified as M, son of R and a student of Class II at a private school.

50 days ago, when M and 4 of his friends were playing on the street, a stray dog bit them.

A villager said while 4 of the boys were administered anti-rabies vaccines, M's parents took him to a man who practised herbal medicine.

The boy started behaving abnormally a few days ago and was taken to the Institute of Child Health and Hospital for Children, Egmore. The victim's health began deteriorating on Saturday [21 Aug 2021], and he died without responding to treatment.

His body has been handed over to the health staff of Chennai Corporation for safe disposal at a burial ground in Mylapore [Tamil Nadu].

--
