[HealthMap/ProMED map of South Africa: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8626789,3070

Around 99% of human cases of rabies are due to bites from infected dogs. Controlling and eradicating rabies, therefore, means combatting it at its animal source. For OIE's communication campaign "Rabies ends here" toolkit, please refer to https://trello.com/b/66Bqv1ld/world-rabies-day-toolkit. - Mod.AS]

["From 1960 to 2018, 127 human rabies cases were reported in the United States, with roughly a quarter resulting from dog bites received during international travel. Of the infections acquired in the United States, 70% were attributed to bat exposures" (https://www.cdc.gov/rabies/location/usa/surveillance/human_rabies.html). - Mod.ML]
